ZH: 他比我年长十岁。
EN: He is ten years older than me.

ZH: 她的姐姐比她年长五岁。
EN: Her sister is five years older than her.

ZH: 我的爷爷年长九十岁了。
EN: My grandfather is ninety years old.

ZH: 我们应该尊重年长者。
EN: We should respect our elders.

ZH: 她是我们学校年长的教师之一。
EN: She is one of the older teachers in our school.

ZH: 有些人年长了，但依然精力充沛。
EN: Some people are older but still full of energy.

ZH: 年长并不代表不聪明。
EN: Being older does not mean being unintelligent.

ZH: 在中国文化中，年长者享有更高的地位。
EN: In Chinese culture, older people hold a higher position.

ZH: 年长者应该给予年轻人更多的指导和支持。
EN: Older people should provide more guidance and support to the younger generation.

ZH: 老师在班级中是年长者的代表。
EN: Teachers represent the older generation in the class.

ZH: 她比她的弟弟年长两年。
EN: She is two years older than her younger brother.

ZH: 比起年长，重要的是经验和智慧。
EN: Experience and wisdom are more important than age.

ZH: 年长并不意味着一定拥有更高的工作地位。
EN: Being older does not necessarily mean having a higher position at work.

ZH: 年长者可以通过传授经验帮助年轻人成长。
EN: Older people can help younger people grow by sharing their experiences.

ZH: 我希望能够活到年长的年纪。
EN: I hope to live to a ripe old age.

ZH: 年长者的聪明才智是我们应该借鉴的。
EN: We should learn from the wisdom of our elders.

ZH: 年长者常常具有丰富的人生经验。
EN: Older people often have a wealth of life experience.

ZH: 年长者的建议是宝贵的财富。
EN: The advice of older people is a valuable asset.

ZH: 在中国传统文化中，年长者被孝敬和尊重。
EN: In traditional Chinese culture, older people are revered and respected.

ZH: 年长者是社会的重要资源。
EN: Older people are an important resource for society.
